author: Alexander Forbes
comment: I enjoyed watching Ahsoka grow and mature as a character over the years, I think she was in a really good place by the end of the Clone Wars in terms of character realization. However, I think they took it a bit too far, she's become too much like the Republic era jedi that she saw the flaws in and left, too dispassionate, too aloof. I'm not really interested in Ahsoka if she's got ice water in her veins. Honestly, I think the full realization of the character would have been more like Kanan, a spouse, a parent, AND a jedi knight. Show that it's possible to be a jedi and still be a person, fundamentally I think that's the take away from Anakin's story. If he hadn't been stifled by the jedi's dogmatic ways he could have been an incredible force for good, but instead he had to live in secret and as a result had no support system when he was in crisis, he took the only hand extended to him, Palpatine's, and the galaxy suffered. It's also the cause for most jedi that go dark, you can live a disciplined and principled life and still let yourself feel things and form attachments.
